summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsVegan20 million+ bottles sales, and counting! ma:nyo Pure Cleansing Facial Oil is a gentle yet powerful cleansing oil that melts away blackheads and whiteheads without clogging pores.
details: DetailsFeaturesThis effective oil cleanser contains 14 plant-derived oil to allow moisturizing skin while cleansing without clogging pores (Non-comedogenic).It transforms into a luscious milk that dissolves makeup and impurities while restoring skin's natural moisture and pH balance.It is suitable for all skin types, including acne-prone skin.Key IngredientsArgan Kernel Oil - Known for its nourishing power, and it effectively regulates amounts of sebum and helps regenerate skin cells.Jojoba Seed Oil - Full of vitamins and omega that replenish the moisture level on the skin.Olive Oil - Rich in vitamin E and reduces excessive facial oil.Formulated WithoutFragranceSiliconParabenItem 2626991How To UseTake 2-3 pumps of cleansing oil into dry palms and gently massage over the face.Add water to emulsify and rinse thoroughly with lukewarm water.IngredientsGlycine Soja (Soybean) Oil, Corylus Avellana (Hazel) Seed Oil, Sorbeth-30 Tetraoleate, Vitis Vinifera (Grape) Seed Oil, Olea Europaea (Olive) Fruit Oil, Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride, Squalane, Isoamyl Laurate, Camellia Japonica Seed Oil, Oenothera Biennis (Evening Primrose) Oil, Simmondsia Chinensis (Jojoba) Seed Oil, Helianthus Annuus (Sunflower) Seed Oil, Argania Spinosa Kernel Oil, Orbignya Oleifera Seed Oil, Saponaria Officinalis Leaf Extract, Camellia Sinensis Leaf Extract, Oryza Sativa (Rice) Bran Oil, Rice Ferment Filtrate (Sake), Decyl glucoside, Ginkgo Biloba Leaf Extract, Lavandula Angustifolia (Lavender) Oil, Aloe Barbadensis Leaf Extract, Citrus Aurantium Dulcis (Orange) Oil, Melaleuca Alternifolia (Tea Tree) Leaf Oil, Tocopherol.
how_to_use: Take 2-3 pumps of cleansing oil into dry palms and gently massage over the face.Add water to emulsify and rinse thoroughly with lukewarm water.

faceoff_positive.comments:
A Gentle Yet Mighty First Cleanse (5/5 Stars)
As someone who prioritizes effective yet gentle skincare, I'm always on the hunt for a cleansing oil that truly delivers. The ma:nyo Pure Cleansing Oil has not only met but exceeded my expectations, quickly becoming a holy grail in my daily routine.
What it is: This is a lightweight, oil-based cleanser designed to be the first step in a double cleansing routine. It's formulated with a blend of natural oils (like argan, jojoba, and soybean) and is free from mineral oil, artificial fragrances, and artificial colors, which is a huge plus for those with sensitive skin.
First Impressions & Texture: The oil itself has a wonderfully light, almost watery consistency, which makes it a joy to massage into the skin. It feels incredibly smooth and non-greasy, a common concern with some cleansing oils. There's a very subtle, natural scent that quickly dissipates, another win for sensitive noses.
Performance & Efficacy: This is where the ma:nyo Pure Cleansing Oil truly shines.
 * Melts Makeup Effortlessly: From stubborn waterproof mascara and eyeliner to long-wear foundation and sunscreen, this oil effortlessly dissolves everything. A gentle massage for about 30 seconds is all it takes to see makeup emulsify and lift away.
 * Emulsifies Beautifully: When you add a bit of water, the oil transforms into a milky emulsion that rinses cleanly without leaving any greasy residue. This is crucial for a cleansing oil, as no one wants a film left behind.
 * Non-Stripping & Hydrating: Unlike some cleansers that leave your skin feeling tight and dry, the ma:nyo Pure Cleansing Oil leaves my skin feeling soft, supple, and hydrated. It never feels stripped or irritated, which is a testament to its gentle formulation.
 * Helps with Blackheads/Congestion: I've also noticed a subtle improvement in the appearance of my blackheads and overall skin texture since incorporating this into my routine. The oil seems to gently dislodge impurities, contributing to clearer pores over time.
Who is it for?
I wholeheartedly recommend this cleansing oil to:
 * Anyone who wears makeup, even light makeup or just sunscreen.
 * Individuals looking for an effective first cleanse in a double cleansing routine.
 * Those with sensitive, dry, or combination skin types.
 * Anyone seeking a gentle yet powerful makeup remover that won't strip their skin.
Overall Verdict: The ma:nyo Pure Cleansing Oil is a standout product in the crowded world of cleansing oils. Its ability to effortlessly remove makeup and impurities while leaving skin feeling clean, soft, and nourished makes it an absolute must-have. It's a fantastic investment for anyone looking to elevate their cleansing routine.
Rating: 5/5 Stars

faceoff_negative.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] For me, this product caused a mild stinging feeling on my face. The smell isn't terrible but has a bit of a tea tree smell. From what I'm reading it has a lot of natural ingredients. The packaging is appealing and the pump is super convenient. I used this product for about a week. The stinging sensation continued with each use. I feel like I had more breakouts using this product. It did make removing makeup sooooo easy though so that is definitely a benefit to this product. I have combination nature skin. So this isn't for me. I feel like someone with dry skin might benefit from from this.  The consistency is thick so it's good for use as a dry cleanse. So use it with out water first. Then gradually add water while working in to remove build up. Then rinse thoroughly. Then follow up with other your everyday cleanser.
